==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mohair
<hw>Mo"hair`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>moire</ets>,
perh. from Ar. <ets>mukhayyar</ets> a kind of coarse camelot or
haircloth; but prob. fr. L. <ets>marmoreus</ets> of marble, resembling
marble. Cf. <er>Moire</er>, <er>Marble</er>.]</ety> <def>The long silky
hair or wool of the Angora goat of Asia Minor; also, a fabric made from
this material, or an imitation of such fabric.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mohammed</ent>⟦br⟧
